OL,3,CArtificial pancreas to be given to
OL,4,Cwomen with diabetes to cut pregnancy
OL,5,Crisks
OL,7,FAbout 400,000 people in the UK have
OL,8,Ftype 1 diabetes, a lifelong condition
OL,9,Fin which the immune system attacks
OL,10,Finsulin-producing cells in the
OL,11,Fpancreas.
OL,13,FInsulin helps the body use sugar for
OL,14,Fenergy, and without it, blood sugar
OL,15,Flevels can rise dangerously.
OL,17,FPeople with type 1 diabetes must
OL,18,Fcarefully manage their blood sugar to
OL,19,Fkeep their levels within range,
OL,20,Fusually through insulin injections or
OL,21,Fpumps.
