OL,3,CArtificial pancreas to be given to
OL,4,Cwomen with diabetes to cut pregnancy
OL,5,Crisks
OL,7,FDuring her first pregnancy, she relied
OL,8,Fon finger-prick glucose tests and an
OL,9,Finsulin pump every hour by day and
OL,10,Fevery 30 minutes overnight.
OL,12,FHer baby girl then needed a week in
OL,13,Fneonatal intensive care for jaundice,
OL,14,Fweight issues and other complications.
OL,16,FDuring her second pregnancy, Ms Willer
OL,17,Fused the artificial pancreas and no
OL,18,Flonger needed constant monitoring. Her
OL,19,Fsecond daughter was born healthy at 36
OL,20,Fweeks.
